details.address: 300 Technology Center Way Suite 200, Rock Hill, SC 29730
details.description: A coffee cafe merging robotic innovation with a premium espresso experience in a modern and inviting atmosphere. Our robotic barista does all the work while you get to enjoy. The elegant industrial vibe offers an elevated style and experience from the moment you enter the doors. Multiple seating areas, an open layout, 20-foot concrete columns and windows as far as the eye can see that provide a stunning backdrop. We also offer pastries made by local bakers.

reviews_data.review_text: So the café sucks like really bad...

The cortado was delicious. We went for the novelty of watching a high tech machine make sophisticated coffee drinks and discovered a very inviting venue for relaxing, conversing, or reading while enjoying a seriously good espresso beverage. It was a delight to meet the owners Keith and Chauntel.

I needed a place to post up and work remotely this past week, and this was the perfect spot. It's very cozy with lots of seating, free wifi, and relaxing atmosphere. Parking is close by and free in the parking garage. The owners were hanging out in the Cafe most of the time I was there and were very kind and welcoming. The robotic coffee is a neat concept and simple to use, and really hit the spot! The drink options are simple and I appreciated having a menu that didn't have 100 different ways to customize your drinks. I find other chains make their lattes too sweet, but theirs was the perfect balance of flavor. I really look forward to returning in the future when I need to work outside of the home. It's definitely a hidden gem!
Yesterday i had a portrait done there lets is quiet and relaxing.  The owners are great Boston Bruins fans .

simple, easy, relaxing and clean! definitely a new study spot for me! plenty of seating and even a more private area for meetings or large study groups. extremely friendly staff which is always amazing!
We have been a few times. The drinks are good. Love the environment. The owner is usually present and keeps things clean

I had to give it a star to comment

We would LOVE to try this place, but their hours are bad.

We want coffee after dinner. Can't go here because they close at 7.

Was gonna go there on a Sunday. Nope. Closed at 5.

Which makes no sense. It is a computerized, automated. Non-human operation. Why are the hours so bad?

Do the research. Go watch starbucks and other competitors. See the business you are missing out on.
Didn't like the coffee. All I wanted was a decaf with cream. Only thing I could find was an expresso Americana.
This coffee shop not only has good coffee but is a fun experience. I do with they had more options for iced coffees and food.

review_questions.Parking options: Free street parking, Free parking garage

reviews_data.review_text: Great coffee. Cool concept!

I love the atmosphere here, it's a great place to come work for a few hours or hang out and read a book. Having pastries from local bakeries is such a great concept. There's gluten-free options from Wild Flour, so good! Definitely give this place a try.
Great place to sit and work or have a convo with friends. All drinks made by a machine but good stuff. Highly recommend!

Atmosphere is excellent. Lots of natural lighting. Comfortable seating. Great place to relax, meet, or study.

Owners have been in both times I went and were incredibly friendly, interesting, and generous.
The coffee here is amazing. The area has a very modern & cozy vibe. Owners are enjoyable to chat!

Atmosphere was spot on for me, was just put off by the coffee. It wasn’t bad; minimal bitterness, good overall taste, but just not strong enough. Limited options for customization was a huge influence  as well.

I love working from cafés, and Techno Café checks all the boxes—strong Wi-Fi, plenty of space, and a great atmosphere that doesn’t feel crowded. The coffee is consistently good, which I really appreciate. While the food could be a bit fresher, it didn’t take away from the experience. I’m glad to have this new spot in Rock Hill and look forward to returning for both the coffee and the quiet thinking space.

What a fun space! Lots of seating options, even private spaces for a quiet cup of coffee. Coffee is great and the gluten free/dairy free muffin from Wild Flour Bakery was delicious. Owners are super friendly and make you feel right at home.
This is a must-visit spot in Rock Hill. If you are looking for a quality cup of coffee along with a cozy atmosphere you have to check this out.

Such an amazing spot! The atmosphere is warm and welcoming, and the coffee is fantastic. It’s the perfect place to get work done, relax with friends, or even host a meeting in their spacious conference area. I also think the robotic coffee machines are super cool and neat!
Love. The vibe

Chai latte was delicious! Seeing your coffee made by a machine is really cool lol. We so luckily got to meet the owner, she was so welcoming & down to earth. Definitely give this place a try! The prices are reasonable & the space is beautiful.
Amazing coffee, gorgeous and relaxing space.
